    <stitle>ALTERNATOR: DELCO-REMY 20-SI SERIES, TYPE 300 (BRUSHLESS)</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsection id="s08013" svcsectype="prodspec" division="truck" formnum="CTS-5038" date="03/31/1996">
        <title>ALTERNATOR: DELCO-REMY 20-SI SERIES, TYPE 300 (BRUSHLESS)</title>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <vendorgroup/>

                <vendor>DELCO-REMY</vendor>
                <truckmodelgroup/>

                <truckmodel>3000</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>4000</truckmodel>
                <ucodegroup/>

                <ucode>08GAR</ucode>
                <vendcodegroup/>

                <vendcode>20-SI</vendcode>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <lev1>
                    <table id="hl0801301">
                        <title>Code Table</title>
                        <tgroup cols="2">
                            <colspec colname="1" colwidth="2.75in"/>
                            <colspec colname="2" colwidth="2.75in"/>
                            <spanspec namest="1" nameend="2" spanname="s1t2"/>
                            <thead>
                                <row rowsep="0">
                                    <entry colname="1">
                                        <para>Code</para>
                                    </entry>
                                    <entry colname="2">
                                        <para>Rating</para>
                                    </entry>
                                </row>
                            </thead>
                            <tbody>
                                <row rowsep="0">
                                    <entry colname="1">
                                        <para>08gar</para>
                                    </entry>
                                    <entry colname="2">
                                        <para>60 AMP</para>
                                    </entry>
                                </row>
                            </tbody>
                        </tgroup>
                    </table>
                </lev1>
                <lev1>
                    <para>The 20-SI series alternator shown in
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f0801301">Figure 1</hotlnk>and
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f0801302">Figure 2</hotlnk>is a brushless unit featuring a built-in voltage
                        regulator. The only movable part in the assembly is the rotor, which is mounted on a ball
                        bearing at the drive end, and a roller bearing at the rectifier end. All current-carrying
                        conductors are stationary. These conductors are the field winding, the stator windings, the six
                        rectifying diodes, and the regulator circuit components.
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f0801301" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g0801301" filename="../figg08/G0801301.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                        <caption>20-S1 Series Alternator</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1. "POS" (OUTPUT) TERMINAL</callout1>
                            <callout1>2. "R" (RELAY) TERMINAL</callout1>
                            <callout1>3. GROUND SCREW</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                    <figure id="f0801302" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g0801302" filename="../figg08/G0801302.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                        <caption>Cross Sectional View of Alternator</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1. ROLLER BEARING</callout1>
                            <callout1>2. GREASE RESERVOIR</callout1>
                            <callout1>3. REGULATOR</callout1>
                            <callout1>4. FIELD COIL</callout1>
                            <callout1>5. STEEL THREAD INSERT</callout1>
                            <callout1>6. BALL BEARING</callout1>
                            <callout1>7. LABYRINTH SEAL</callout1>
                            <callout1>8. FELT SEALS</callout1>
                            <callout1>9. ADJUSTABLE BUSHING</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                </lev1>
                <lev1>
                    <para>A fan located on the drive end provides air flow for cooling. The bearings are sealed so no
                        periodic lubrication is required.
                    </para>
                </lev1>
                <lev1>
                    <para>Only one wire is needed to connect the alternator to the battery, along with an adequate
                        ground return. An "R" terminal is provided for use in some circuits to operate auxiliary
                        equipment.
                    </para>
                </lev1>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
